  • Add 1ts of sugar plus the yeast to 2,5dl of warm water.
  • Dice the potato, and in a small pot boil it in approx. 1,5dl of water with 1ts of salt for 20 minutes.
  • Mash the potato in that remaining water that it was boiling in, and let it cool.
  • When the yeast is ready, add the mixture to the flour, the mashed potato and add 1ts of salt. Stir until a smooth dough forms.
  • Place it to a warm place.
  • Grade the garlic into the sour cream, add a pinch of salt and pepper, and stir well.
  • Chop the onions into half circles, add some salt and sugar.
  • Chop the sausage into circles, the ham into short sticks.
  • Dice and bake the bacon in a pen. Use the leftover fat to create a non-sticky surface on the baking sheet.
  • Make the dough into two portions, and roll them into 1-2cm thick, then place them on the baking sheets. Pierce them with a fork, and wait for a couple of minutes.
  • Bake them for 5-6 minutes in a pre-warmed oven on 200°C.
  • Spread a layer of the garlic sour cream, put the ham, the sausage, the bacon and the onion on top, and bake it for another approx. 15 minutes.
  • Put a thick layer of cheese on top, and bake it until it gets crispy.
  • Serve it while it’s still hot!

    • ]]>     For the dough:

    50 dkg flour

    20 dkg potato

    25 g yeast

    2.5 dl water (warm)

    1 teaspoon sugar

    1 teaspoon salt

    2 tablespoons olive oil

     

    For the topping:

    2 dl sour cream

    3 cloves garlic

    1 pinch of salt and pepper

    5 dkg ham

    10 dkg sausage (eg. Chorizo)

    3 dkg smoked bacon

    2 big purple onions

    20 dkg cheese (graded)
